Record

public Record(java.lang.Class<T> fields)
Constructs a new Record that represents the fixed fields indicated by the fields parameter. The record way is RecordWay.IN. The lenght of this record is calculated with the sum of the lenght of every field. The value of every field is initialized with a default value (if present)

fields - the fields of this Record

Record

public Record(RecordWay recordWay,
              java.lang.String record,
              java.lang.Class<T> fields,
              java.lang.Integer recordLen,
              java.util.List<FieldExtendedProperty> fieldExtendedProperties)
Constructs a new Record that represents the fixed fields indicated by the fields parameter. The record way is initialized with the value of the recordWay parameter. The length of the record is initialized with the value present in the recordLen parameter. The value of every field is initialized with the formatted value present in the relative position of the record parameter. To every field of the record are applied the extended properties present in the fieldExtendedProperties parameter. Only the following properties are permitted at record level:
  • FieldExtendedPropertyType.LPAD
  • FieldExtendedPropertyType.RPAD
  • FieldExtendedPropertyType.VALIDATOR

Parameters:
recordWay - the way of this record
record - the formatted string of this Record
fields - the fields of this Record
recordLen - the lenght of this Record
fieldExtendedProperties - the extended properties of field applied to every fields of the record

toRemoveAccents

public void toRemoveAccents()
Apply the method toRemoveAccents to the value of every field of type FieldType.AN of this record.

Every character with accent present in the value of a field of type FieldType.AN, is replaced with the relative character without accent. For example the character is replaced with the character a

toRemoveAccents

public void toRemoveAccents(FieldProperty fieldProperty)
Apply the method toRemoveAccents to the value of the field of type FieldType.AN represented by the fieldProperty param

Every character with accent present in the value of the field of type FieldType.AN, is replaced with the relative character without accent. For example the character is replaced with the character a

resetStatus

public void resetStatus()
